            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Prepaid expenses are amounts paid in advance for a benefit the business will receive in a later period, carried as a current asset until used. Insurance of Rs 24,000 paid on 1 January for twelve months leaves Rs 18,000 prepaid at 31 March, with only Rs 6,000 charged to the profit and loss statement for that year."
