        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the difference between direct expenses and indirect expenses?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Direct expenses can be traced to a specific product, job or service and are charged to the trading account, such as raw material, factory wages and carriage inward. Indirect expenses support the business as a whole and go to the profit and loss statement, such as rent, audit fees and office salaries. The split drives gross profit."
          }
