            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Cash payments above Rs 10,000 to one person in a single day are disallowed under Section 40A(3). Payments where TDS was not deducted or not deposited attract a 30 per cent disallowance under Section 40(a)(ia). Personal expenses, income tax itself and penalties for breaking the law are also disallowed, so book profit rarely equals taxable profit."
